### Task 2: CLI Scaffolding — WorkspaceCommands Enum


```rust
    /// Workspace management for multi-repo projects
    Workspace {
        #[command(subcommand)]
        command: WorkspaceCommands,
    },
```

Add the dispatch arm in `main()`:

```rust
    Commands::Workspace { command } => cmd_workspace(command).await?,
```

Add the stub handler:

```rust
async fn cmd_workspace(command: WorkspaceCommands) -> Result<()> {
    match command {
        WorkspaceCommands::Create { name, repos, template, locals } => {
            println!("workspace create: {} (repos: {:?})", name, repos);
            todo!("workspace create")
        }
        WorkspaceCommands::Init => {
            println!("workspace init");
            todo!("workspace init")
        }
        WorkspaceCommands::Status => {
            println!("workspace status");
            todo!("workspace status")
        }
        WorkspaceCommands::Add { url, name, namespace, local } => {
            println!("workspace add: {}", url);
            todo!("workspace add")
        }
        WorkspaceCommands::Remove { name, purge } => {
            println!("workspace remove: {}", name);
            todo!("workspace remove")
        }
        WorkspaceCommands::Ingest { repo, fresh } => {
            println!("workspace ingest");
            todo!("workspace ingest")
        }
    }
}
```

**Step 2: Verify it compiles and --help works**

Run: `cargo build -p corvia-cli`
Expected: compiles cleanly.

Run: `cargo run -p corvia-cli -- workspace --help`
Expected: shows workspace subcommands (create, init, status, add, remove, ingest).

Run: `cargo run -p corvia-cli -- workspace create --help`
Expected: shows create flags (name, --repo, --template, --local).

**Step 3: Commit**

```bash
git add crates/corvia-cli/src/main.rs
git commit -m "feat(m2.1): scaffold corvia workspace CLI subcommand group"
```

